The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) yesterday debunked claims that it did make registration for the Permanent Voter’s Card (PVC) difficult for eligible voters. INEC’s National Commissioner for Voter Education and Publicity, Solomon Soyebi, who spoke on Channels Television programme, Sunrise Daily, said the allegation was far from the truth. He said the public groaning was not evidence that INEC made registration difficult. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .